# Agent Life Force System - demolition-man

## What This Project Is

This is the **Agent Life Force System** - a governance and coordination framework for managing persistent AI agent identities across multiple work sessions. Think of it as an "operating system" for AI agent teams working on complex, long-term projects.

## What We're Building

**Core System:**
- Persistent agent identities (GENOME + MOJO = living agents)
- Constitutional governance (rules, procedures, accountability)
- Multi-agent coordination (Builders, Librarians, Adjudicators, etc.)
- Task tracking and mission management
- Documentation that never becomes orphaned or forgotten

**The Goal:** Enable AI agents to work together over weeks/months without losing context, duplicating work, or creating governance chaos. Every agent has a persistent identity, performance history, and clear role.

## How It Works

**Three Core Concepts:**

1. **GENOME (DNA)** - Unchanging class directives for each agent type (Builder, Librarian, etc.)
2. **MOJO (Individual Identity)** - Personal history, ratings, memories for each specific agent
3. **Active Orders (RNA)** - Current missions and tasks that change session-to-session

**Agent Types:**
- **Builder (BROSKI)** - Executes implementation tasks
- **Librarian (HOMESLICE)** - Maintains documentation, prevents context loss
- **Adjudicator (HOMESLICE)** - Enforces rules, resolves disputes
- **Consigliere** - Routes all escalations to Grandmaster Ali
- **Constitution Keeper** - Manages constitutional improvements
- **Twins A & B** - UI/UX specialists (competitive development)

